  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Somalia: Strengthening the Social Contract through Access to Justice in Somaliland</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To improve access to an alternative dispute resolution mechanism and referral pathways, especially for vulnerable groups. 2) To enhance access to formal justice for vulnerable groups through holistic support to gender-based violence (GBV) survivors and affected communities. 3) To increase participation of citizens of Somaliland in accountability processes relating to the provision of security and justice.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Direct beneficiaries: Somaliland population, specifically, women, girls, GBV survivors and those at risk of GBV, internally displaced persons (IDPs), youth, religious leaders and community elders, rural communities and minority social groups.
Indirect beneficiaries: Civil society and legal aid organisations, as well as Somaliland justice chain institutions (Ministry of Justice, Ministry of Interior, Ministry of Employment, Social and Family Affairs, Courts, Police, the Attorney General&#x2019;s Office and members of Parliament), and hospitals offering one stop centers.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to improve social contract through increased legimitacy of justice sector institutions in Somaliland.</narrative>
  </description>
